I decided to go with a theme based on one of my favorite games. My goal was to give people the feel for speed as these marbles go careening down the track!

This is my land conversion and major update of my original glass_villafinal.  It's no longer symmetrical, and I've made sure it's optimized to its fullest.  I've included many props to make it more realistic, and done what I can to create variety.  The house has three rooms and two entrances to the main level.  A door can be broken to get into the basement, or you can go down one of the two ladders on the main floor (one at the bottom of the tower, one behind the bar).  There is also a secret tunnel, but you'll have to find it yourself.  The ivy on the tower can be climbed to get to the roof, as can the ivy along the eaves above the parlor balcony and the hedge maze.  The only other way to get up to the roof is by the crates at the Terrorist spawn.  The Terrorist team spawns on either side of the building, while the Counter-Terrorists spawn in the small cluster of trees at the bottom of the hill leading to the villa.  No bomb site, no hostages; the only way to win is to defeat the opposing team.  Have fun.

--(MM)ABOUT deLiGHT's Muscle Memory Map Pack For a complete understanding of deLiGHT's muscle memory maps, check out this. Maps are made on the Source engine to reduce eye strain, but should benefit players from all versions assuming values are consistent across platforms. --(MM)ABOUT David "deLiGHT" Light David "deLiGHT" Light is a freelance eSports writer and aspiring professional Counter-Strike player. He encourages you to perform #drexel on GameSurge to support his efforts in return for this contribution. --(MM)CONTENTS Two muscle memory maps, example.avi, a listenserver.cfg and a quick and easy desktop practice executable. --(MM)INSTALL 1. Place the cstrike folder inside youraccount\Counter-Strike source\ (overwrite where necessary) 2. Right click the MM Practice shortcut (after extracting to desktop), and go to properties. 3b. In the line "Target:" ensure the path to your steam.exe is correct. 3c. In the "Start in:" line, ensure the path to your Steam folder is correct, and apply. ** If you would like to change the map the practice shortcut starts, adjust the target line accordingly. --(MM)PLAY Start the practice by executing the MM Practice shortcut. Note: The listenserver.cfg changes your mat_dxlevel to 90. If you normally play CS:S with a different value, do the following: Add the launch options command -dxlevel X to your "My Games" CS:S launch options (ex. -dxlevel 81) This will ensure everytime you start up CS, outside of the practice shortcut, you have dxlevel 81. Also note that crosshair scale is adjusted to 1200 for ease of use in listenserver.cfg --(MM)QUESTIONS Q: Is there a 1.6 version of these MM maps? A: Yes, there is, but only Source versions are distributed becuase they are less intensive on the eyes. When CSP has a stable release, I'll look to recreate/port the maps for convenience when possible. Q: Do I shoot the targets or just aim at them? A: Just aim. Mimicking the shooting process is important however. My advice is to empty the m4a1 and turn up the in-game sound loud enough for the "click" of missing ammo to be heard over mp3s. Source crosshairs react as if a gun was fired, even if no bullets are in the clip. This gives the effect of shooting, without dealing with messy bullet holes or stuttering recoil delay. I wouldn't click for every point, but rather only for a specific ring of colors or two. Q: How long does it take to complete each MM map? A: A 20-30 minute program would generally consistent of 250 reps per point on mm_8, or 25 reps per point on mm_64 (give or take 15min, depending on the speed). Q: What is a "rep" in this situation? A: A rep is full movement from the center point to the specified point, and back again to the center. Q: May I decompile the map to change the colors of the points? A: Sure, I don't mind. Just limit it to personal use (as to avoid confusion of proper version). The colors are currently not as varied now, because only limited default textures can be seen effectively without individual adjustments to lighting (afaik). Q: I've designed a nice logo for the shortcut. How can I contact you about it? A: See the Support section below. Q: May I host this file? A: Anyone and everyone is free to host this file, as long as it is free of charge and the contents are left unedited and fully intact. --(MM)SUPPORT Any questions or concerns (technical or otherwise) please direct them to deLiGHT in #drexel on GameSurge.

Mi_training_final Readme

When this map loads on your server it will password protect your server. 

The password is - clantrainingmap

It also changes the following cvars on the server

roundtime 9
autoteambalance 0
bot_quota 0
mp_buytime 60
mp_startmoney 16k
sv_password is set as above

The above cvar's will go back to your server config when the map is finished or changed.


Map Discription

Main Area:-
You spawn in a small - medium Mirrored area with many places where you can hide behind 
to snipe your enemy from and so on. 


There are 4 other areas you can move to via the relvant doors (you get teleported). In 
the box in the middle of the map there is a hidden breakable floor that has my clan logo 
on it's floor. This is awsome 
to hide inside and shoot ppl as they run past.

Range1:-
Range 1 is a massive rifle range that allows you to practice with each gun available 
in the game. When you enter each booth a red light comes on outside above the doorway to 
show there is someone in there. You will be stripped of weapons and you will find 2 buttons - 
the first on the shelf gives you the gun (it has a timer so multiple weapons can be spawned);
the second (on the wall) moves the target. You press this multiple times to set the distance -
there are 4 set positions but u can press it while moving at any time to stop it. This range 
is excellent for showing the different effect each weapon will have when fired over
different distances. the teleport in has a 2 second delay to help reduce getting stuck.

Range2:-
When you enter this section you will see 4 mini ranges - 

the first is a nade throwing
 exercise and the dummies disaper when you hit them; 
the second is a target range when you hit the bull on the target a box pops down
and there is a spining target than can be set at 3 difficulty levels;
the third is another type of spinning target with dummies that disappear when you hit them
and again this can be set at 3 different difficulty levels;
the forth is a moving target, when you hit the dummies they disappear and this again
can be set at 3 difficulty levels.

Sniper pit:-
This area is a clone of the pit from dust2 but in a mirror style setup. The distance is the same 
as if you were awping to site A when you go in this area you have to get the awp from the 
dispenser and take out the enemy CT spawn one side and T the other.

Area1
This is a massive area, CT spawn one side and T the other. There is a table with a button to get 
your weapon. The idea is to improve your skills with m4/ak over a distance.


Known Bugs - 

The nade area of the map can be seen from a certain point from the main area
